Method Detail

addExit

public void addExit(Room e,
                    java.lang.String direction)
Adds an exit for this room. Since the exits are stored in a HashMap, if two exits are supposed to have the same direction (e.g. Room1 is UP from this room and Room2 is UP from this room as well) then only the second room is kept in memory (e.g. Room2).

Parameters:
e - Room instance of the exit
direction - direction it is from the room.

getExit

public Room getExit(java.lang.String where)
Returns the exit for the given direction. Warning: this function returns a null pointer if there is no exit for the given direction.

Parameters:
where - direction as a string
Returns:
the exit for the given direction

getExitsFormatted

public java.lang.String getExitsFormatted()
Returns the list of exits for this room. A typical exit is formatted as: exit:NAME. Exits in all directions are printed, the name is null if there is no exit.

Returns:
the list of exits formatted (in raw data).
